pullRequest.body:
We add a separate file in which the set of symbols of a FreeMonoid element is defined. This is separated so that users of the basic FreeMonoid file need not unnecessarily import the finiteness hierarchy (as symbols is defined as a Finset)

```suggestion
Authors: Hannah Fechtner
```
I think that this is one of the linter's complaints.
yup :) before it wasn't even getting to that, so this is some progress, at least!

I'm confused what `to_additive` does here, if `symbols` itself hasn't been `to_additive`ized.
Could you please add the attribute to all declarations in this file?

If some definition hasn't been additivised, then it is simply kept invariant when translating

Of course that is not what we want to do here

I messed up - I used open instead of namespace, and then to resolve the errors, I fussed with the `to_additive`

It's fixed now! (thanks to adomani)

I'm going to guess that this should be a `namespace`, rather than `open`.

As a consequence, the `to_additive` of `symbols` would have to be defined separately (I think that only theorems/lemmas are auto-generated by `to_additive`).
aha! thank you so much, that was my error when separating this out from the main file

If you `namespace` everything, then `to_additive` will generate an additivized name for this that will be `FreeAddMonoid.mem_symbols` or something like this, that will differ from the multiplicative name in the namespace and will not create a clash.

```suggestion
theorem symbols_mul {a b : FreeMonoid α} : symbols (a * b) = symbols a ∪ symbols b := by
```
I still don't quite buy that argument, @jcommelin. The only extra thing it imports is `Finset`. If that's too much, then we should be working on it rather than artificially splitting later files
